    en: "New York Real Property Tax Law Section 459-c authorizes a partial real property tax exemption of up to 50 percent of a primary residence's assessed value for homeowners with a qualifying disability and limited income. Each town, village, city, county, and school district decides whether to offer the exemption and sets its own income cap within the range allowed by RPTL 459-c. A qualifying homeowner files Form RP-459-c with the local assessor by the taxable status date (March 1 in most Monroe County municipalities). The exemption is renewed annually on Form RP-459-c-Rnw. Proof of disability is satisfied by an SSA disability award, VA disability rating, Railroad Retirement Board disability, or a physician's certification on the NY form. The current state-allowed range and Monroe County adopted caps are at the Monroe County Office of Real Property Tax Services and at tax.ny.gov."
